Alternatively, you can use the viewport height (vh) and viewport width (vw) units to set the background to cover the entire page:
```css
body {
  margin: 0;
  padding: 0;
  background-color: #e8e8e8;
  font-family: 'DM Sans',sans-serif;
  text-align: center;
  /* Add these lines */
  height: 100vh;
  width: 100vw;
}
```

This will set the height and width of the body to be 100% of the viewport height and width, respectively, ensuring that the background covers the entire page without any margins or paddings.

Either approach will work, but the second approach using `vh` and `vw` units is simpler and more commonly used.
